From: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
Date: Thu, 10 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sound: fix PipeWire audio hang via hw_constraint_list in asoc_simple_startup

PipeWire's SPA ALSA plugin probes the device using an open-ended rate
interval (rate min=0, max=INT_MAX).  When snd_pcm_hw_params() is called
with a rate that has not been constrained via snd_pcm_hw_params_set_rate*,
params_rate(params) returns INT_MAX (2147483647).  This value falls
through to the default case in the asoc_simple_hw_params() rate switch:

  [22.816054] sunxi:sound-mach:[ERR]: 87 asoc_simple_hw_params(): Invalid rate 2147483647
  sunxi-snd-plat-i2s-sunxi-snd-codec-av: ASoC: error at snd_soc_link_hw_params: -22
  sunxi-snd-plat-i2s-sunxi-snd-codec-av: ASoC: error at __soc_pcm_hw_params: -22

PipeWire's ALSA sink then enters an error state.  EmulationStation (which
uses SDL2+PipeWire for audio) blocks indefinitely waiting for the sink to
become ready, freezing the entire UI.  This manifests as a hard freeze
whenever ES tries to play a sound (navigation, game launch, media preview).

Fix by registering a rate constraint list in asoc_simple_startup() that
exactly mirrors the cases handled by asoc_simple_hw_params().  This causes
snd_pcm_hw_refine() to intersect PipeWire's open interval down to the
valid rate set before hw_params is ever called, so params_rate() always
returns a valid rate (e.g. 48000).

Tested on Radxa Cubie A7S (Allwinner A733 / sun60iw2).
---
 bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_mach.c | 22 ++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_mach.c b/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_mach.c
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_mach.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_mach.c
@@ -30,10 +30,30 @@ static LIST_HEAD(extparam_list);

 #define DRV_NAME	"sunxi-snd-mach"

+static const unsigned int sunxi_mach_rates[] = {
+	8000, 11025, 12000, 16000, 22050, 24000,
+	32000, 44100, 48000, 64000, 88200, 96000, 176400, 192000,
+};
+
+static const struct snd_pcm_hw_constraint_list sunxi_mach_rate_constraints = {
+	.count	= ARRAY_SIZE(sunxi_mach_rates),
+	.list	= sunxi_mach_rates,
+};
+
 static void asoc_simple_shutdown(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream)
 {
 }

 static int asoc_simple_startup(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream)
 {
 	struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd = substream->private_data;
 	struct asoc_simple_priv *priv = snd_soc_card_get_drvdata(rtd->card);
-	if (priv->wait_time)
+	int ret;
+
+	ret = snd_pcm_hw_constraint_list(substream->runtime, 0,
+					  SNDRV_PCM_HW_PARAM_RATE,
+					  &sunxi_mach_rate_constraints);
+	if (ret < 0)
+		return ret;
+
+	if (priv->wait_time)
 		sunxi_adpt_wait_time_conv(substream, priv->wait_time);
 	return 0;
 }
